The secret of the splendor on Norway solved: the Russians tested a missile
On Norway a special lighting effect of unknown origin was observed.
The Russian Defence Ministry acknowledged yesterday that near the border with Norway it made tests of an intercontinental ballistic missile.
The missile, "Bulava" type, previously intended to be the pride of the Russian army, is becoming the nightmare of the Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimir Putin.
Not even their repeated presence in the missile tests has had the desired effect on the success of the test flights.
Bulavá, in most cases, did not fly out or a failure in the air occurred.
In Russian newspapers they write about "Bulavá" as "a missile that doesn't fly."
A missile that doesn’t fly, but shines.
During this, the 13th test, no problem occurred at the beginning.
At the end of the flight there were again technical problems in the apparatus.
The engine probably exploded in the third stage of the missile.
This time "Bulavá" was launched from the nuclear submarine Dmitry Donskoy, which floated immersed in the White Sea.
This type of missile enables the launch from a ship that is moving and is immersed at the same time.
That’s why the mysterious light on Norway, caused by an unidentified flying object, is likely to actually be the failed “Bulavá”.
The Norwegians even from the beginning didn’t hesitate that it was a Russian missile.
The generals this time defend themselves saying that one can’t just talk about a failure.
The first two stages of the missile ended and the failure occurred in the third.
In the previous cases, the engines disrupted immediately in the first stage.
Although none of the launches passed completely without errors, according to the Ministry of Defense management only six of the thirteen were failed.
The success of almost a fifty percent is full of optimism to the generals and therefore they continue to say that "Bulavá" one day will fly without problems and that it will even succeed in carrying up to ten hypersonic nuclear blocks, whose total maximum weight is 1.15 tons.
